The police in Lagos have arraigned three men for allegedly diverting 3,000 cartons of noodles valued at N8.85 million. They were arraigned at the weekend before Chief Magistrate Shomade of Randle Court One on five counts of conspiracy, obtaining by false pretences, theft, forgery and alteration of document. Police said the defendants committed the offence last month at Apapa by conniving with others now at large to divert a container carrying the goods which belonged to Olam Sanyo Foods Ltd. The defendants pleaded not guilty to the charges and were admitted to bail in the sum of N3m each with two sureties in like sum. The court adjourned the case till August 10.